        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 8 at 4:00PM EDT by NWS Gaylord MI</headline>
        <description>At 359 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Curran, or 14 miles southwest of The Town Of Hubbard Lake, moving
east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Spruce, Barton City, Curran, Hubbard Lake, and Mitchell Township.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
